# Help: kexec and crash-dump (kdump) infrastructure
#
# KEXEC and KEXEC_FILE provide the syscalls that load a second
# kernel image into reserved memory; CRASH_DUMP reserves that
# memory and arranges for the secondary kernel to boot into it
# on panic for post-mortem analysis via kdump. PROC_VMCORE is
# the /proc file the post-panic kernel uses to expose the crashed
# kernel's memory to userspace (makedumpfile, crash utility).
# CRASH_HOTPLUG updates the reserved memory region when CPU or
# memory hotplug events change the machine topology.
#
# Every symbol is bool. No builtin/ counterpart needed.
# See: kernel/kexec/Kconfig
# See: https://docs.kernel.org/admin-guide/kdump/kdump.html

CONFIG_KEXEC=y
CONFIG_KEXEC_CORE=y
CONFIG_KEXEC_FILE=y
CONFIG_CRASH_DUMP=y
CONFIG_CRASH_RESERVE=y
CONFIG_CRASH_HOTPLUG=y
CONFIG_CRASH_MAX_MEMORY_RANGES=8192
CONFIG_PROC_VMCORE=y
